1
00:00:34,490 --> 00:00:36,850
Soon, you’ll encounter something unexpected.

2
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:38,560
Conflict.

3
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:41,070
Arguments with a woman

4
00:00:41,070 --> 00:00:42,940
or an old karmic debt.

5
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:49,420
You may face a major change.

6
00:00:51,450 --> 00:00:53,230
The Tower card says…

7
00:00:53,230 --> 00:00:55,340
that this change

8
00:00:55,340 --> 00:00:57,570
will be like building a tower.

9
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:03,950
It won’t be easy.

10
00:01:05,250 --> 00:01:06,260
Quite dangerous.

11
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:12,770
Before it’s complete,

12
00:01:14,050 --> 00:01:15,650
it’ll take some time.

13
00:02:51,150 --> 00:02:53,360
Trying to kill her like this.

14
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:55,790
How rotten are you?!

15
00:02:56,660 --> 00:02:58,410
Help me.

16
00:02:58,410 --> 00:03:00,830
Use the Krishna Kali spell on him!

17
00:03:00,830 --> 00:03:02,230
I don’t want to die!

18
00:03:05,650 --> 00:03:07,130
Please save Lord Gaew.

19
00:03:07,130 --> 00:03:08,890
He’s not breathing anymore.

20
00:03:11,050 --> 00:03:11,820
What?

21
00:03:12,180 --> 00:03:13,280
What’s happening?

22
00:03:13,630 --> 00:03:14,910
Am I dead?

23
00:03:15,090 --> 00:03:16,530
You’re talking nonsense

24
00:03:16,530 --> 00:03:17,770
like a lunatic.

25
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:21,600
Rich!

26
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:23,360
Help me.

27
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,520
I want to get out of here.

28
00:03:27,430 --> 00:03:28,490
Rich?

29
00:03:28,490 --> 00:03:29,829
Don’t you hear me?

30
00:03:30,350 --> 00:03:31,660
Stop calling me so casually.

31
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:35,230
I’m Lord Muen Reung Ratchaphakdi.

32
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:37,420
What are you up to, Rich?

33
00:03:38,450 --> 00:03:41,270
Will you stop being insolent, Gaew?

34
00:03:43,210 --> 00:03:44,030
Rich.

35
00:03:44,380 --> 00:03:45,510
What the hell?

36
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:47,090
Quit playing around.

37
00:03:47,090 --> 00:03:49,420
Come with me to the police department.

38
00:03:49,420 --> 00:03:50,850
What police department?

39
00:03:51,540 --> 00:03:52,760
I’m confused.

40
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:54,260
Such insolence.

41
00:03:55,280 --> 00:03:57,870
Arrest him, Muen Reung.

42
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:59,090
Yes.

43
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,920
This is ridiculous, Aunt.

44
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:02,030
Who is Gaew?

45
00:04:03,380 --> 00:04:04,450
Everyone.

46
00:04:05,060 --> 00:04:06,160
Listen to me.

47
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:08,510
My name…

48
00:04:08,510 --> 00:04:09,680
is Great.

49
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:11,600
Great what?

50
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:14,010
Stop talking nonsense.

51
00:04:14,570 --> 00:04:15,360
Take him away.

52
00:04:15,980 --> 00:04:16,790
What are you doing?

53
00:04:17,329 --> 00:04:17,930
Hey!

54
00:04:18,450 --> 00:04:19,180
Let go of me.

55
00:04:19,180 --> 00:04:20,089
Why are you arresting me?

56
00:04:20,089 --> 00:04:21,180
I didn’t do anything wrong.

57
00:04:21,180 --> 00:04:21,870
Let go!

58
00:04:21,870 --> 00:04:23,460
My lord.

59
00:04:23,460 --> 00:04:25,210
Juang’s bleeding won’t stop.

60
00:04:28,930 --> 00:04:31,420
Let go. Let me go.

61
00:04:31,420 --> 00:04:33,409
Let go. I’m a doctor!

62
00:04:33,409 --> 00:04:34,600
Let go.

63
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:36,170
Gaew.

64
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:38,159
I think he’s gone mad.

65
00:04:38,159 --> 00:04:39,970
He’s even claiming to be a doctor.

66
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:42,860
Juang.

67
00:04:46,090 --> 00:04:47,210
Wake up.

68
00:04:48,860 --> 00:04:50,070
My lady.

69
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:52,200
Please save my grandson.

70
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:56,340
Why are you all standing still?

71
00:04:56,340 --> 00:04:58,070
Go get a doctor!

72
00:04:58,070 --> 00:04:59,100
-Go!
-Yes, ma’am.

73
00:05:00,250 --> 00:05:01,620
No need to go.

74
00:05:01,620 --> 00:05:02,730
I’ll handle this.

75
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:10,490
Juang has arterial bleeding.

76
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:12,960
That’s why he’s bleeding this much.

77
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:14,700
We need to control the blood pressure.

78
00:05:14,860 --> 00:05:16,500
What are you talking about?

79
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:17,890
So strange.

80
00:05:17,890 --> 00:05:18,920
Right?

81
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,750
Acting like a doctor all of a sudden.

82
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:24,340
Let him try, Mother.

83
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:26,520
If you make a mistake,

84
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:28,870
I will never forgive you.

85
00:05:29,530 --> 00:05:30,820
This is a man’s life,

86
00:05:30,820 --> 00:05:31,890
not a toy.

87
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:34,040
I know a person’s life isn’t a toy.

88
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:37,280
Do you have any gauze?

89
00:05:39,020 --> 00:05:40,220
I mean clean cloth.

90
00:05:41,010 --> 00:05:41,730
Yes, we do.

91
00:05:42,010 --> 00:05:43,980
Bring me clean cloth and water.

92
00:05:43,980 --> 00:05:45,340
I’m going to clean his wound.

93
00:05:45,340 --> 00:05:46,100
Yes, sir.

94
00:05:58,300 --> 00:05:59,520
Excuse me.

95
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:38,980
Help me lift his legs.

96
00:06:52,140 --> 00:06:53,850
Keep his legs up high.

97
00:06:53,850 --> 00:06:55,200
It’ll slow the bleeding.

98
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,480
This way, he’ll lose less blood.

99
00:07:14,610 --> 00:07:16,860
Even if you manage to save Juang,

100
00:07:17,820 --> 00:07:20,530
he hurt this much because of you!

101
00:07:21,330 --> 00:07:22,110
Reung.

102
00:07:22,460 --> 00:07:24,920
Take him to the police department.

103
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:26,430
Punish him.

104
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:31,280
And take Yam, his wretched servant, with him!

105
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:33,810
Gaew.

106
00:07:39,090 --> 00:07:40,450
I didn’t do anything wrong.

107
00:07:40,450 --> 00:07:41,770
I’m not going anywhere.

108
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,810
If you didn’t do it,

109
00:07:44,810 --> 00:07:46,590
then how did my boat sink?

110
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:48,200
How would I know?

111
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:49,860
I haven’t even seen a single boat.

112
00:07:51,060 --> 00:07:51,940
Reung.

113
00:07:52,610 --> 00:07:54,060
Why are you still standing there?

114
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:58,100
You have to come with me.

115
00:07:58,100 --> 00:07:59,490
I didn’t do anything wrong.

116
00:07:59,490 --> 00:08:01,020
Let go. Let go!

117
00:08:01,150 --> 00:08:01,890
Reung.

118
00:08:02,410 --> 00:08:03,120
Let me go.

119
00:08:04,580 --> 00:08:06,120
It’s already late.

120
00:08:07,090 --> 00:08:08,590
You can go get some rest.

121
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:11,080
That won't do, Dech.

122
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:13,670
They need to take him in for questioning.

123
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:14,900
Mother.

124
00:08:14,900 --> 00:08:16,060
Tomorrow morning,

125
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:19,520
I’ll take Gaew to the police department myself.

126
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:21,560
-But I think…
-Jumpa!

127
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:33,740
That’s fine, Dech.

128
00:08:42,539 --> 00:08:44,039
Then I’ll take my leave.

129
00:08:58,140 --> 00:08:58,810
Gaew.

130
00:09:00,050 --> 00:09:00,850
Come with me.

131
00:09:02,610 --> 00:09:04,260
Come here.

132
00:09:04,650 --> 00:09:05,880
Where are you taking me?

133
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:07,130
My lord.

134
00:09:07,130 --> 00:09:08,910
I’m not Gaew. I’m Great!

135
00:09:21,020 --> 00:09:23,960
I’m the reason you’re not arrested tonight.

136
00:09:24,420 --> 00:09:25,180
So,

137
00:09:25,890 --> 00:09:26,930
be good

138
00:09:27,740 --> 00:09:29,290
and don’t cause any trouble.

139
00:09:29,290 --> 00:09:31,860
Or I won’t be able to help you anymore.

140
00:09:35,650 --> 00:09:36,310
Hey.

141
00:09:37,130 --> 00:09:38,580
Are you not going to tell me

142
00:09:39,020 --> 00:09:40,340
who you people are?

143
00:09:40,340 --> 00:09:41,570
Where is this place?

144
00:09:41,570 --> 00:09:42,530
And what do you want?

145
00:09:43,930 --> 00:09:45,250
You talk strangely.

146
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,250
You.

147
00:09:48,410 --> 00:09:50,710
Aren’t you going to tell me who you are?

148
00:09:50,710 --> 00:09:52,140
Don’t call me “Khun.”

149
00:09:52,790 --> 00:09:53,800
I’m merely a "Muen."

150
00:09:54,710 --> 00:09:55,640
What’s a "Muen"?

151
00:09:55,640 --> 00:09:59,750
(‘Khun’ means ‘You’, but it’s also a high lord title.)
(Muen ranks lower than Khun.)

152
00:10:00,020 --> 00:10:01,240
You're acting cool, huh?

153
00:10:01,310 --> 00:10:03,970
('Thumb Song' means 'acting cool', but 'Song' is also a royal prefix.)

154
00:10:03,970 --> 00:10:04,480
“Song”?

155
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:05,960
What do you mean?

156
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:07,900
Song is a royal prefix.

157
00:10:08,770 --> 00:10:09,900
If other people overhears that,

158
00:10:10,410 --> 00:10:11,890
your head will roll.

159
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:13,220
Jeez.

160
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:14,960
Why so fierce.

161
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:16,560
Fierce?

162
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:18,600
I’m not fierce.

163
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:20,920
This isn’t fierce?

164
00:10:21,470 --> 00:10:24,100
You’re frowning and scowling.

165
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:26,220
Are you criticizing me?

166
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:29,360
No. I’m just telling the truth.

167
00:10:30,010 --> 00:10:31,060
Then,

168
00:10:31,060 --> 00:10:32,620
I’ll call you…

169
00:10:32,620 --> 00:10:33,730
P’Muen.

170
00:10:33,730 --> 00:10:34,660
Okay?

171
00:10:35,340 --> 00:10:36,120
Okay?

172
00:10:36,810 --> 00:10:37,800
What does “okay” mean?

173
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,730
Okay means agreed.

174
00:10:42,700 --> 00:10:43,800
Such a strange word.

175
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:45,470
You make no sense.

176
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:48,840
It’s as if you’re possessed.

177
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:52,440
Yam.

178
00:10:52,890 --> 00:10:53,470
Yes, sir.

179
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:54,960
Keep a close eye on your master.

180
00:10:55,380 --> 00:10:56,010
Yes, sir.

181
00:11:02,850 --> 00:11:03,950
Oh, right.

182
00:11:04,370 --> 00:11:05,320
What’s your name?

183
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:08,130
Me?

184
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:09,320
Yes.

185
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:11,450
There’s only the two of us here.

186
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,570
My lord.

187
00:11:13,820 --> 00:11:15,560
You even forget my name?

188
00:11:16,130 --> 00:11:17,560
My name is Yam.

189
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:18,770
Yam.

190
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:20,820
What era are we in right now?

191
00:11:22,260 --> 00:11:22,840
Era?

192
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:25,020
What’s an era?

193
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:28,370
I mean the reign.

194
00:11:33,410 --> 00:11:34,550
Which reign is this?

195
00:11:35,450 --> 00:11:36,710
You mean who's our ruler?

196
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:39,100
Yeah, who is it?

197
00:11:39,540 --> 00:11:41,610
Our ruler is Khun Luang Narai, sir.

198
00:11:42,420 --> 00:11:44,380
Khun Luang Narai?

199
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,220
Khun Luang Narai.

200
00:11:48,550 --> 00:11:49,630
King Narai?

201
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:51,600
Huh?

202
00:11:52,780 --> 00:11:54,900
Did I really travel back more than 300 years?

203
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:01,650
My lord. My lord.

204
00:12:02,510 --> 00:12:03,290
My lord.

205
00:12:14,790 --> 00:12:15,960
I can’t figure out

206
00:12:16,620 --> 00:12:18,670
why the Krishna Kali spell…

207
00:12:18,670 --> 00:12:20,390
affected Gaew like this.

208
00:12:23,670 --> 00:12:24,600
I think

209
00:12:26,140 --> 00:12:28,570
we may have been wrong from the start.

210
00:12:29,830 --> 00:12:31,710
Maybe Gaew isn’t the culprit.

211
00:12:33,310 --> 00:12:37,390
How could it not be him?

212
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:39,990
But Gaew is completely unharmed.

213
00:12:40,590 --> 00:12:43,380
He just seems insane, right?

214
00:12:48,670 --> 00:12:50,820
The fact that Gaew is still alive

215
00:12:50,820 --> 00:12:52,410
means that he

216
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:54,330
is innocent.

217
00:12:55,190 --> 00:12:56,810
The Krishna Kali spell

218
00:12:57,240 --> 00:13:00,590
cannot harm an innocent person.

219
00:13:03,850 --> 00:13:05,830
But what surprises me is…

220
00:13:07,710 --> 00:13:09,710
He’s not the same Gaew as before.

221
00:13:10,300 --> 00:13:11,240
Isn’t that right?

222
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:46,780
Finally, it's morning.

223
00:13:47,780 --> 00:13:49,740
What a crazy dream.

224
00:14:11,140 --> 00:14:11,850
Whoa!

225
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:20,520
Am I still dreaming?

226
00:14:23,570 --> 00:14:25,120
But if this is real,

227
00:14:27,430 --> 00:14:29,210
then how did I get here?

228
00:14:34,810 --> 00:14:35,640
Where’s the mirror?

229
00:14:41,370 --> 00:14:42,090
What?

230
00:14:52,580 --> 00:14:54,810
Whose body is this?

231
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:56,840
My lord.

232
00:14:57,070 --> 00:14:59,700
You even forgot who you are.

233
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,430
If I could travel back in time,

234
00:15:09,760 --> 00:15:11,360
then I must be able to go back.

235
00:15:14,570 --> 00:15:16,210
But how do I go back?

236
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:21,760
I don’t even know how I got here.

237
00:15:32,580 --> 00:15:34,160
Grandma’s probably stressed out

238
00:15:34,740 --> 00:15:36,880
that her blood pressure has risen.

239
00:15:52,340 --> 00:15:53,050
Hey.

240
00:15:53,850 --> 00:15:54,990
Where’s the bathroom?

241
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:56,560
Bathroom?

242
00:15:57,140 --> 00:15:58,990
What’s a bathroom?

243
00:15:59,740 --> 00:16:01,310
The place where you pee and poop.

244
00:16:02,690 --> 00:16:03,810
Right here.

245
00:16:03,810 --> 00:16:04,910
The chamber pot.

246
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:10,910
You expect me to pee in it?

247
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:13,120
This is insane.

248
00:16:13,680 --> 00:16:14,760
I need to take a dump.

249
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:16,330
This way, sir.

250
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:19,040
Lord Gaew.

251
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:26,940
This way, sir.

252
00:16:27,340 --> 00:16:27,890
Where?

253
00:16:30,100 --> 00:16:30,820
Stop!

254
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:35,150
I knew you’d try to run away.

255
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:37,510
Nonsense. I’m not running away.

256
00:16:37,510 --> 00:16:38,020
Let’s go.

257
00:16:38,020 --> 00:16:39,690
Stop! Where are you going?

258
00:16:40,070 --> 00:16:40,870
To the toilet.

259
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:42,010
The toilet?

260
00:16:42,620 --> 00:16:44,620
What’s a toilet, and what do you do there?

261
00:16:45,530 --> 00:16:46,590
To take a dump.

262
00:16:46,590 --> 00:16:47,390
Come on, Yam.

263
00:16:47,670 --> 00:16:48,950
Hey, Gaew.

264
00:16:51,360 --> 00:16:52,940
Gaew will escape through the vej.

265
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:54,860
(Vej is an ancient Thai toilet.)

266
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:56,760
This way, sir.

267
00:16:58,490 --> 00:17:00,100
Here is the vej.

268
00:17:01,980 --> 00:17:02,640
"Vej"?

269
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:04,710
As in wet?

270
00:17:06,589 --> 00:17:08,040
It’s not wet, sir.

271
00:17:09,660 --> 00:17:11,760
People actually poop here?

272
00:17:12,069 --> 00:17:13,740
Yes, we poop here.

273
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:28,790
Hmm.

274
00:17:29,660 --> 00:17:30,950
Luxurious.

275
00:17:32,550 --> 00:17:33,830
Luxurious?

276
00:17:34,310 --> 00:17:35,990
What does that mean?

277
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:38,740
He really forgot everything.

278
00:17:41,140 --> 00:17:43,150
He doesn’t even recognize a vej.

279
00:17:43,820 --> 00:17:44,960
Goodness.

280
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:50,550
I feel much better.

281
00:18:00,170 --> 00:18:00,830
P’Yam.

282
00:18:01,310 --> 00:18:01,950
I’m done.

283
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:03,550
Where’s the toilet paper?

284
00:18:04,860 --> 00:18:05,580
Toilet paper?

285
00:18:06,670 --> 00:18:07,840
What’s that?

286
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:09,370
You know,

287
00:18:09,370 --> 00:18:10,680
paper for wiping your butt.

288
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:13,070
Well…

289
00:18:13,790 --> 00:18:15,710
it's that bamboo tube over there.

290
00:18:23,780 --> 00:18:25,020
This one?

291
00:18:25,020 --> 00:18:26,350
Isn't it a fortune stick?

292
00:18:27,140 --> 00:18:28,910
That’s not a fortune stick.

293
00:18:28,910 --> 00:18:30,670
It’s a butt wiping stick.

294
00:18:36,070 --> 00:18:37,740
A butt wiping stick?

295
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:41,850
Wouldn’t it tear your butt apart?

296
00:18:51,660 --> 00:18:52,410
Hey.

297
00:18:55,150 --> 00:18:56,390
Why are you following me?

298
00:18:57,040 --> 00:18:57,660
Well…

299
00:18:58,490 --> 00:18:59,660
I thought you’d run away.

300
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:02,070
I’m not running away.

301
00:19:02,590 --> 00:19:03,840
I’m here to poop.

302
00:19:15,940 --> 00:19:17,850
P'Yam, I need to wash up.

303
00:19:17,850 --> 00:19:19,070
This way, sir.

304
00:19:22,070 --> 00:19:22,710
Hey!

305
00:19:23,620 --> 00:19:25,020
Why are you pulling my clothes?

306
00:19:30,650 --> 00:19:31,910
Can’t bear it?

307
00:19:32,420 --> 00:19:33,600
I haven’t washed my butt.

308
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:36,990
-Come on, P’Yam.
-This way, sir.

309
00:19:46,470 --> 00:19:47,690
He’s strange.

310
00:19:48,650 --> 00:19:49,830
More like insane.

311
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:01,000
P’Yam.

312
00:20:01,530 --> 00:20:02,960
What’s this stick for?

313
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:06,030
It’s a toothbrush stick.

314
00:20:06,030 --> 00:20:07,910
We use it with ash and salt.

315
00:20:12,520 --> 00:20:13,270
What about...

316
00:20:14,140 --> 00:20:15,270
this round thing?

317
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:17,840
Soapberry, sir.

318
00:20:18,630 --> 00:20:20,390
For scrubbing your body.

319
00:20:20,870 --> 00:20:22,780
Soapberry?

320
00:21:09,540 --> 00:21:10,270
Ah!

321
00:21:27,780 --> 00:21:29,980
That Muen acting cool.

322
00:21:29,980 --> 00:21:31,160
Who is he?

323
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:32,260
Acting cool?

324
00:21:33,280 --> 00:21:35,380
Lord Muen’s name is Dech.

325
00:21:37,800 --> 00:21:39,360
You really forgot everything.

326
00:21:40,420 --> 00:21:41,820
Come on, P’Yam.

327
00:21:41,820 --> 00:21:43,340
People forget things.

328
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:44,990
So,

329
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:47,030
who is Gaew?

330
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:47,680
Huh?

331
00:21:48,540 --> 00:21:49,930
You’re Gaew.

332
00:21:50,660 --> 00:21:53,610
Have you really lost your memory?

333
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:56,230
I’m getting worried.

334
00:21:57,270 --> 00:21:57,920
Okay.

335
00:21:58,330 --> 00:21:59,430
I’m Gaew.

336
00:21:59,930 --> 00:22:00,700
Then,

337
00:22:01,050 --> 00:22:02,330
where are my parents?

338
00:22:02,890 --> 00:22:04,720
Your parents passed away.

339
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:07,640
Your father was Lord Ramnarong.

340
00:22:07,640 --> 00:22:09,320
Your mother was Pudjeeb,

341
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:11,190
a relative of Lady Jumpa,

342
00:22:12,300 --> 00:22:13,950
who's Lord Muen’s mother.

343
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:22,200
My head hurts.

344
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:13,470
Nice build.

345
00:23:13,910 --> 00:23:15,030
That poser.

346
00:23:17,770 --> 00:23:18,630
What did you say?

347
00:23:20,330 --> 00:23:21,880
I said you’re handsome.

348
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:23,860
I’m giving you a like.

349
00:23:25,110 --> 00:23:26,110
What’s a like?

350
00:23:27,310 --> 00:23:28,040
Nothing.

351
00:23:28,760 --> 00:23:29,670
It’s nothing.

352
00:23:34,390 --> 00:23:35,420
Pin, bring the clothes.

353
00:23:46,140 --> 00:23:48,020
Hurry up and get dressed.

354
00:23:48,020 --> 00:23:50,430
You’re coming to the police department with me.

355
00:24:05,910 --> 00:24:06,990
What’s that sound?

356
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:09,800
My stomach is growling.

357
00:24:10,580 --> 00:24:11,900
I’m getting hungry.

358
00:24:12,660 --> 00:24:14,250
I’ll go get your clothes first.

359
00:24:33,110 --> 00:24:34,010
All done.

360
00:24:47,390 --> 00:24:49,210
Now that’s more like it.

361
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:51,160
I look more like Great now.

362
00:24:56,920 --> 00:24:57,840
What’s up, P’Yam?

363
00:24:57,840 --> 00:24:59,120
Hurry up. I’m hungry.

364
00:24:59,120 --> 00:24:59,840
Yes, sir.

365
00:25:06,390 --> 00:25:09,070
Don’t run, my lord

366
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:10,200
Wow.

367
00:25:10,660 --> 00:25:11,940
The table’s loaded.

368
00:25:14,940 --> 00:25:16,180
Where are your manners?

369
00:25:18,020 --> 00:25:19,030
Sorry.

370
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:20,430
Sorry.

371
00:25:23,980 --> 00:25:24,800
Come.

372
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:26,260
Have breakfast with us.

373
00:25:27,060 --> 00:25:29,530
Thank you. I’m starving.

374
00:25:31,930 --> 00:25:33,370
Hey, Pin!

375
00:25:33,630 --> 00:25:34,230
Yes?

376
00:25:35,670 --> 00:25:36,740
Why aren't you moving?

377
00:25:37,350 --> 00:25:39,670
Go get Gaew a plate!

378
00:25:39,670 --> 00:25:40,320
Yes, sir.

379
00:25:55,360 --> 00:25:56,750
That’s right.

380
00:25:57,280 --> 00:25:57,900
Alright.

381
00:25:58,670 --> 00:25:59,610
You may eat now.

382
00:26:00,170 --> 00:26:00,940
Let's eat.

383
00:26:22,180 --> 00:26:25,210
So people here still eat with their hands?

384
00:26:27,750 --> 00:26:29,200
If not with your hands, then what?

385
00:26:29,200 --> 00:26:30,190
Our feet?

386
00:26:31,100 --> 00:26:32,240
Prik!

387
00:26:34,890 --> 00:26:35,910
Auntie.

388
00:26:36,490 --> 00:26:37,980
Please let me finish first.

389
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:40,260
I was going to say that

390
00:26:40,260 --> 00:26:42,900
eating with your hands is actually good.

391
00:26:43,380 --> 00:26:45,140
It stimulates digestion

392
00:26:45,140 --> 00:26:47,190
through sensing the food’s temperature.

393
00:26:47,710 --> 00:26:50,270
It helps improve mindfulness while eating

394
00:26:50,730 --> 00:26:52,820
and strengthens the connection

395
00:26:52,820 --> 00:26:54,850
between us and our food.

396
00:26:55,070 --> 00:26:57,030
And it helps improve blood circulation.

397
00:26:57,910 --> 00:26:59,400
There he goes again.

398
00:26:59,900 --> 00:27:00,550
Good grief.

399
00:27:00,710 --> 00:27:01,430
What a weirdo.

400
00:27:02,600 --> 00:27:05,100
It’s not strange, Jumpa.

401
00:27:05,360 --> 00:27:06,660
It’s called Ayurveda.

402
00:27:31,540 --> 00:27:32,830
You’re eating like a baby.

403
00:27:33,220 --> 00:27:34,420
Making such a mess.

404
00:27:34,960 --> 00:27:37,340
At this rate, Yam might have to feed you.

405
00:27:37,980 --> 00:27:39,000
Come on.

406
00:27:59,380 --> 00:28:00,150
Argh!

407
00:28:00,710 --> 00:28:01,870
I’ll excuse myself.

408
00:28:02,070 --> 00:28:04,150
I can’t stand him.

409
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:09,680
Prik, let’s go back to my room.

410
00:28:09,680 --> 00:28:10,780
Yes, my lady.

411
00:28:22,020 --> 00:28:22,830
Your water, sir.

412
00:28:23,100 --> 00:28:24,080
It’s rainwater.

413
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:31,340
So refreshing.

414
00:28:31,700 --> 00:28:34,030
I’ve never had anything like this.

415
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:38,670
I usually only drink mineral water.

416
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:40,280
Huh?

417
00:28:41,770 --> 00:28:42,630
Mineral water?

418
00:28:47,950 --> 00:28:48,680
Yes.

419
00:28:50,650 --> 00:28:51,570
Go get ready.

420
00:28:51,990 --> 00:28:54,280
You have to come to the police department with me.

421
00:29:02,270 --> 00:29:05,190
Muen Reung sent word that Lord Gaew

422
00:29:05,190 --> 00:29:07,090
doesn’t need to go to the police department.

423
00:29:07,430 --> 00:29:08,020
Huh?

424
00:29:08,230 --> 00:29:09,110
Don’t “huh”.

425
00:29:09,390 --> 00:29:10,710
Go tell your master.

426
00:29:10,710 --> 00:29:11,590
Yeah, yeah.

427
00:29:16,090 --> 00:29:16,960
Pin.

428
00:29:16,960 --> 00:29:17,660
Yes, sir.

429
00:29:23,450 --> 00:29:24,220
P’Yam.

430
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:25,930
Let me ask you something.

431
00:29:27,750 --> 00:29:29,450
Why does P’Muen hate me so much?

432
00:29:30,230 --> 00:29:33,280
You and Lord Muen never got along.

433
00:29:33,280 --> 00:29:35,870
Every time you meet, you end up arguing.

434
00:29:36,590 --> 00:29:40,160
Because Lord Muen is sharp

435
00:29:40,810 --> 00:29:42,760
more intelligent,

436
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:44,200
and he's a skilled swordsman.

437
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:47,400
So you always lose to him.

438
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:50,720
I…

439
00:29:51,100 --> 00:29:53,680
I’m sorry. I deserve to die.

440
00:29:53,680 --> 00:29:54,990
Please beat me all you want,

441
00:29:54,990 --> 00:29:57,270
but please don’t send me to the slave quarters.

442
00:29:57,780 --> 00:29:58,400
Hey.

443
00:29:59,180 --> 00:30:00,150
I'm not angry.

444
00:30:01,150 --> 00:30:02,280
Go on.

445
00:30:02,970 --> 00:30:05,830
What else did I do to make him hate me?

446
00:30:06,630 --> 00:30:07,680
Give me the worst one.

447
00:30:08,510 --> 00:30:09,690
The worst one?

448
00:30:10,250 --> 00:30:10,810
Yes.

449
00:30:11,830 --> 00:30:15,440
You ordered me to sink his boat.

450
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:17,540
But that day, Lady Jumpa was on the boat.

451
00:30:20,540 --> 00:30:21,230
Dech.

452
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:22,490
Reung.

453
00:30:23,130 --> 00:30:24,560
Have they found Noi’s body?

454
00:30:24,960 --> 00:30:26,170
She’s not dead.

455
00:30:26,510 --> 00:30:27,770
A villager rescued her.

456
00:30:27,770 --> 00:30:29,620
She’s at Phanan Choeng temple now.

457
00:30:29,620 --> 00:30:31,830
But she’s still not making any sense.

458
00:30:31,830 --> 00:30:34,330
Maybe because she was underwater for too long.

459
00:30:37,620 --> 00:30:38,730
In that case, Gaew…

460
00:30:40,300 --> 00:30:42,810
He won’t have to be punished for causing someone’s death.

461
00:30:50,020 --> 00:30:52,520
What happened at your house last night, Dech?

462
00:30:52,920 --> 00:30:55,590
Why do I feel like Gaew has changed?

463
00:30:57,600 --> 00:30:58,920
I’m not sure yet.

464
00:31:08,670 --> 00:31:10,230
Did he really try to kill someone?

465
00:31:12,060 --> 00:31:13,220
That’s a grave sin.

466
00:31:16,870 --> 00:31:18,790
Oh, Gaew.

467
00:31:22,540 --> 00:31:24,790
I’ll go refill the tea first.

468
00:31:30,730 --> 00:31:32,200
I can’t stay here.

469
00:31:34,040 --> 00:31:35,270
If I stay any longer,

470
00:31:36,270 --> 00:31:37,590
I’ll be dead for sure.

471
00:31:39,180 --> 00:31:40,550
But how do I get back?

472
00:32:07,950 --> 00:32:09,390
If lightning...

473
00:32:10,620 --> 00:32:12,110
brought me here,

474
00:32:16,330 --> 00:32:18,260
then it could send me back as well.

475
00:32:28,550 --> 00:32:31,580
Come on, strike me!

476
00:32:31,930 --> 00:32:33,430
Come at me.

477
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:41,630
Gaew.

478
00:32:42,250 --> 00:32:43,580
What are you doing, Gaew?

479
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:57,640
Lord Muen.

480
00:33:05,360 --> 00:33:06,440
What are you doing?

481
00:33:07,180 --> 00:33:08,800
What spirit possessed you

482
00:33:08,800 --> 00:33:10,270
to do something like this?

483
00:33:12,500 --> 00:33:13,750
I’m not possessed.

484
00:33:14,510 --> 00:33:15,870
And I’m not insane.

485
00:33:16,800 --> 00:33:19,110
I’m perfectly sane.

486
00:33:19,740 --> 00:33:20,990
Don’t lie to me.

487
00:33:21,310 --> 00:33:22,380
Why are you doing this?

488
00:33:23,530 --> 00:33:24,800
Will you even believe me?

489
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:25,880
Just tell me.

490
00:33:28,940 --> 00:33:30,570
I want lightning to strike me,

491
00:33:30,870 --> 00:33:32,640
so I can go back to where I came from.

492
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:33,300
Huh?

493
00:33:35,990 --> 00:33:37,110
You’ve lost your mind.

494
00:33:37,370 --> 00:33:39,020
Your way of thinking is so strange.

495
00:33:40,360 --> 00:33:41,870
Don’t ever do this again.

496
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:43,210
It’s an order.

497
00:33:43,870 --> 00:33:44,820
Go back inside!

498
00:33:52,830 --> 00:33:54,380
Please head back too.

499
00:33:54,960 --> 00:33:55,910
You’ll catch a cold.

500
00:34:11,860 --> 00:34:13,110
Will you even believe me?

501
00:34:13,110 --> 00:34:14,179
Just tell me.

502
00:34:17,179 --> 00:34:18,650
I want lightning to strike me,

503
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:20,750
so I can go back to where I came from.

504
00:34:25,790 --> 00:34:26,620
Lord Muen.

505
00:34:27,230 --> 00:34:28,880
You look troubled.

506
00:34:29,659 --> 00:34:31,150
What’s wrong?

507
00:34:34,330 --> 00:34:35,380
It’s Gaew.

508
00:34:36,440 --> 00:34:37,870
Something isn’t right.

509
00:34:39,989 --> 00:34:41,920
Did Lord Gaew do something?

510
00:34:44,489 --> 00:34:47,050
Ever since he woke up, he’s been different.

511
00:34:47,739 --> 00:34:48,989
Nothing he says makes sense.

512
00:34:49,659 --> 00:34:50,590
And he seems

513
00:34:51,139 --> 00:34:52,489
to remember nothing at all.

514
00:34:53,580 --> 00:34:54,949
Like a different person.

515
00:34:57,630 --> 00:34:58,950
I totally agree.

516
00:35:00,260 --> 00:35:02,600
Maybe it’s because of the Krishna Kali spell.

517
00:35:04,110 --> 00:35:05,210
That spell is powerful.

518
00:35:06,260 --> 00:35:09,580
Even if it doesn’t kill him, it could drive him insane.

519
00:35:13,070 --> 00:35:14,420
I’m also not sure

520
00:35:15,130 --> 00:35:17,130
what exactly happened to Gaew.

521
00:35:19,310 --> 00:35:21,160
I only hope that

522
00:35:21,160 --> 00:35:22,820
this change

523
00:35:23,830 --> 00:35:25,260
is for the better.

524
00:35:45,350 --> 00:35:46,750
That’s Lord Gaew.

525
00:35:52,670 --> 00:35:53,620
Who is that, P’Yam?

526
00:35:54,410 --> 00:35:55,760
That’s Lord Saen.

527
00:35:55,760 --> 00:35:56,790
Last time,

528
00:35:56,790 --> 00:36:00,650
your fighting rooster beat every one of his.

529
00:36:01,600 --> 00:36:03,580
So he’s very furious.

530
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:08,890
Let’s go, P’Yam.

531
00:36:12,300 --> 00:36:13,210
Where are you going?

532
00:36:13,640 --> 00:36:15,310
Nowhere. Nothing.

533
00:36:16,760 --> 00:36:17,350
Hey!

534
00:36:20,060 --> 00:36:20,950
My lord!

535
00:36:21,520 --> 00:36:22,590
Why’d you kick me?

536
00:36:22,830 --> 00:36:25,480
Last time, your rooster beat all of mine.

537
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:27,740
This time, I won’t let you go.

538
00:36:27,740 --> 00:36:28,680
Where’s your rooster?

539
00:36:28,680 --> 00:36:30,810
Let my Khun Thong stomp it into the ground.

540
00:36:30,810 --> 00:36:32,330
I don’t have a rooster.

541
00:36:32,920 --> 00:36:34,950
And isn’t Khun Thong a bird species?

542
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:36,600
Don’t toy with me.

543
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:39,610
I have to go.

544
00:36:53,770 --> 00:36:55,720
Don’t come any closer.

545
00:36:55,720 --> 00:36:57,110
I’m serious.

546
00:36:57,110 --> 00:36:58,080
Get him!

547
00:37:07,980 --> 00:37:08,800
My lord.

548
00:37:16,760 --> 00:37:17,860
Lord Muen.

549
00:37:18,890 --> 00:37:20,060
Lord Gaew…

550
00:37:20,500 --> 00:37:23,390
This Gaew doesn’t seem like the old Gaew.

551
00:37:24,640 --> 00:37:27,440
If he’s not Lord Gaew, then who is he?

552
00:37:29,830 --> 00:37:31,380
He’s familiar, but not the same.

553
00:37:32,160 --> 00:37:34,580
He’s different , but not that different.

554
00:37:35,670 --> 00:37:36,640
Isn’t that right, Pin?

555
00:37:38,870 --> 00:37:39,930
I’m confused.

556
00:37:50,060 --> 00:37:52,730
It’s been a long time, P’Jumpi.

557
00:37:53,060 --> 00:37:56,220
What brings you all the way here today?

558
00:37:56,650 --> 00:37:59,930
Gaew beat Saen up in the middle of the market.

559
00:38:02,930 --> 00:38:03,830
Good heavens!

560
00:38:07,960 --> 00:38:10,220
How could this happen?

561
00:38:10,220 --> 00:38:11,950
Is Saen alright?

562
00:38:12,360 --> 00:38:14,820
I don’t care how it happened.

563
00:38:15,240 --> 00:38:17,710
You need to deal with him for me.

564
00:38:18,060 --> 00:38:20,800
Don't let him see the light of day again.

565
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:23,180
Saen is your grandson.

566
00:38:23,180 --> 00:38:26,070
Gaew is only a distant relative.

567
00:38:26,070 --> 00:38:28,410
If you keep him in this house,

568
00:38:28,410 --> 00:38:32,510
one day he might betray you.

569
00:38:33,050 --> 00:38:34,350
At this rate,

570
00:38:34,350 --> 00:38:39,180
Gaew might spit in the water

571
00:38:39,180 --> 00:38:42,270
that you drink every day.

572
00:38:42,390 --> 00:38:43,800
For heaven’s sake, Prik!

573
00:38:43,800 --> 00:38:44,910
I’m about to faint.

574
00:38:45,670 --> 00:38:48,100
Throw him out immediately.

575
00:38:48,100 --> 00:38:50,360
Kick him out of the capital.

576
00:38:50,360 --> 00:38:53,750
Make him suffer for all eternity!

577
00:38:57,670 --> 00:39:00,520
We need to talk.

578
00:39:01,590 --> 00:39:05,540
You assaulted Saen, my sister’s son.

579
00:39:06,320 --> 00:39:08,860
And brought shame upon my ancestors

580
00:39:08,860 --> 00:39:11,100
in front of the whole market.

581
00:39:15,190 --> 00:39:16,970
I didn’t mean to hurt anyone.

582
00:39:16,970 --> 00:39:18,660
You didn’t mean to?

583
00:39:18,660 --> 00:39:21,230
You nearly beat him to death!

584
00:39:21,700 --> 00:39:23,120
If he had meant to,

585
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:26,630
wouldn’t he have dug up your ancestors’ bones

586
00:39:26,630 --> 00:39:28,250
and trampled on them?

587
00:39:28,250 --> 00:39:29,250
Prik!

588
00:39:32,860 --> 00:39:34,150
I didn’t start the fight.

589
00:39:34,150 --> 00:39:35,390
He came after me first.

590
00:39:36,150 --> 00:39:38,670
He's just all talk.

591
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:42,330
You all should…

592
00:39:43,900 --> 00:39:44,550
Uh…

593
00:39:45,310 --> 00:39:48,010
Auntie, you should know your nephew well.

594
00:39:48,010 --> 00:39:50,870
And I know you well too, Gaew.

595
00:39:51,930 --> 00:39:54,390
Calm down, Jumpa.

596
00:39:55,130 --> 00:39:57,750
We should hear both sides of the story.

597
00:40:00,180 --> 00:40:04,200
Why don’t we bring Saen and Jumpi here to talk?

598
00:40:04,860 --> 00:40:06,170
Dech, come on.

599
00:40:06,700 --> 00:40:08,310
Deal with him for me.

600
00:40:10,880 --> 00:40:13,030
If things happened the way Mother and Aunt said,

601
00:40:13,030 --> 00:40:14,840
then you deserve punishment.

602
00:40:15,710 --> 00:40:17,550
But I want to hear it from you first.

603
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:19,430
What happened?

604
00:40:21,210 --> 00:40:22,710
I admit

605
00:40:22,710 --> 00:40:24,300
that Saen and I got into a fight.

606
00:40:25,420 --> 00:40:26,420
But what I did,

607
00:40:27,150 --> 00:40:28,620
was for self defense.

608
00:40:29,270 --> 00:40:30,440
I didn’t mean to.

609
00:40:31,540 --> 00:40:32,420
I’m sorry.

610
00:40:43,480 --> 00:40:44,390
I know...

611
00:40:44,800 --> 00:40:46,240
that in the past,

612
00:40:46,240 --> 00:40:47,920
Gaew did many bad things to you guys.

613
00:40:49,310 --> 00:40:50,240
But today,

614
00:40:51,110 --> 00:40:53,100
can I have a chance to become a better person?

615
00:40:54,180 --> 00:40:55,480
There’s no greater kindness

616
00:40:56,620 --> 00:40:58,170
than forgiveness

617
00:40:58,620 --> 00:40:59,660
and a second chance.

618
00:41:09,460 --> 00:41:12,120
That sounds nice coming from him.

619
00:41:12,400 --> 00:41:13,130
Prik!

620
00:41:14,420 --> 00:41:15,310
Yes, ma’am.

621
00:41:16,420 --> 00:41:17,590
If in the past,

622
00:41:18,650 --> 00:41:20,330
I’ve wronged anyone,

623
00:41:21,040 --> 00:41:22,230
whether intentionally

624
00:41:22,820 --> 00:41:23,950
or unintentionally,

625
00:41:25,820 --> 00:41:26,790
I’m sorry.

626
00:41:27,340 --> 00:41:28,330
I really am.

627
00:41:28,870 --> 00:41:30,520
I ask for your forgiveness.

628
00:41:32,280 --> 00:41:33,070
From today on,

629
00:41:33,940 --> 00:41:35,380
I’m a new Gaew.

630
00:42:00,080 --> 00:42:00,840
Juang.

631
00:42:01,130 --> 00:42:01,760
Yes, sir.

632
00:42:02,180 --> 00:42:03,240
Go prepare a boat.

633
00:42:07,350 --> 00:42:09,550
Where are you going?

634
00:42:09,550 --> 00:42:12,400
I’m going to negotiate with Jumpi.

635
00:42:16,520 --> 00:42:18,100
Do you want me to go with you?

636
00:42:19,110 --> 00:42:19,770
No.

637
00:42:21,600 --> 00:42:22,520
Gaew.

638
00:42:22,520 --> 00:42:23,480
Come with me.

639
00:42:29,030 --> 00:42:30,390
Let me handle this for you.

640
00:42:36,860 --> 00:42:40,330
I think Lord Gaew must be possessed,

641
00:42:40,330 --> 00:42:42,430
so he changed drastically.

642
00:42:42,960 --> 00:42:44,590
I think so too, Aunt Prik.

643
00:42:45,020 --> 00:42:47,120
Before, if someone got on his nerves,

644
00:42:47,120 --> 00:42:50,120
he’d kick them, and curse them out like dogs.

645
00:42:50,120 --> 00:42:51,540
But just now,

646
00:42:51,540 --> 00:42:53,480
he knelt down and apologized in tears.

647
00:42:54,280 --> 00:42:55,590
You’re exaggerating.

648
00:42:56,310 --> 00:42:58,230
Did you even see his tears?

649
00:42:58,660 --> 00:43:00,190
I just feel it.

650
00:43:02,880 --> 00:43:03,870
Lord Muen…

651
00:43:04,380 --> 00:43:08,020
also think that Lord Gaew isn’t the same Gaew.

652
00:43:08,970 --> 00:43:10,470
He must be possessed.

653
00:43:10,470 --> 00:43:12,010
Which spirit is this?

654
00:43:12,010 --> 00:43:13,270
I really want to know.

655
00:43:14,070 --> 00:43:15,780
Lord Gaew changed

656
00:43:15,780 --> 00:43:17,320
after recovering from the spell.

657
00:43:17,320 --> 00:43:18,670
All my life,

658
00:43:18,670 --> 00:43:20,620
I’ve only ever heard

659
00:43:20,620 --> 00:43:24,340
that the Krishna Kali spell punishes evil people.

660
00:43:24,340 --> 00:43:26,810
I’ve never heard

661
00:43:26,810 --> 00:43:29,210
it could turn a bad person into a good one.

662
00:43:33,280 --> 00:43:36,350
The servants are gossiping about you.

663
00:43:38,270 --> 00:43:39,710
Let them talk.

664
00:43:40,480 --> 00:43:42,990
They’re doing that because they hate me.

665
00:43:43,390 --> 00:43:44,660
The old Gaew.

666
00:43:45,620 --> 00:43:47,000
What do you mean?

667
00:43:47,380 --> 00:43:48,650
The old Gaew?

668
00:43:50,560 --> 00:43:51,410
It’s nothing.

669
00:43:52,000 --> 00:43:53,100
Go get some sleep.

670
00:43:53,430 --> 00:43:54,490
I’m sleepy.

671
00:43:54,830 --> 00:43:55,530
Yes, sir.

672
00:43:57,790 --> 00:43:58,750
P’Yam.

673
00:43:58,750 --> 00:43:59,530
Yes?

674
00:44:00,490 --> 00:44:01,950
Do you have a mosquito net?

675
00:44:02,380 --> 00:44:04,740
Mosquito nets are only for the masters.

676
00:44:04,740 --> 00:44:07,420
A servant like me doesn't have one.

677
00:44:08,100 --> 00:44:10,910
Aren’t you afraid of getting dengue fever or malaria?

678
00:44:12,010 --> 00:44:13,520
Malaria?

679
00:44:16,250 --> 00:44:17,080
I forgot.

680
00:44:17,750 --> 00:44:19,640
People here don’t know about it yet.

681
00:44:20,000 --> 00:44:21,130
I mean

682
00:44:21,130 --> 00:44:23,550
jungle fever or shaking fever.

683
00:44:23,870 --> 00:44:24,840
Oh.

684
00:44:25,440 --> 00:44:26,110
I see.

685
00:44:26,820 --> 00:44:27,790
You should go to sleep.

686
00:44:28,960 --> 00:44:29,520
Yes, sir.

687
00:44:49,700 --> 00:44:52,680
I brought mosquito nets, pillows, and blankets for you guys.

688
00:44:52,680 --> 00:44:54,890
So you won’t get bitten by mosquitoes.

689
00:44:54,890 --> 00:44:56,150
Everyone can have it.

690
00:44:57,710 --> 00:45:00,040
Your sleeping quarters must be kept clean.

691
00:45:00,040 --> 00:45:02,860
Don’t let dust or water collect anywhere.

692
00:45:02,860 --> 00:45:05,390
So mosquitoes can’t lay eggs and make you sick.

693
00:45:05,390 --> 00:45:07,350
Close the water jars too.

694
00:45:07,350 --> 00:45:09,500
These mosquitoes can kill us.

695
00:45:09,500 --> 00:45:11,150
Don’t leave any standing water around.

696
00:45:11,150 --> 00:45:14,040
If anyone gets bitten and has a high fever,

697
00:45:14,040 --> 00:45:15,280
tell me immediately.

698
00:45:15,910 --> 00:45:17,110
Don’t ignore it.

699
00:45:17,110 --> 00:45:18,790
Lord Gaew handed out mosquito nets,

700
00:45:18,790 --> 00:45:21,150
pillows, and blankets to the servants.

701
00:45:21,150 --> 00:45:23,660
He also told us

702
00:45:23,660 --> 00:45:26,150
to clean our sleeping quarters.

703
00:45:26,330 --> 00:45:30,230
Wasn’t he implying that

704
00:45:30,230 --> 00:45:34,800
P’Hora and I didn’t take good care of the servants?

705
00:45:34,800 --> 00:45:37,660
At this rate, this house will end up becoming his.

706
00:45:39,750 --> 00:45:41,320
He’s being generous.

707
00:45:41,320 --> 00:45:43,190
Why would you hate it?

708
00:45:50,010 --> 00:45:51,980
Good and evil

709
00:45:51,980 --> 00:45:54,760
can’t be forced on

710
00:45:54,760 --> 00:45:56,600
or taken away by others.

711
00:45:57,310 --> 00:45:58,220
Maybe

712
00:45:58,640 --> 00:46:02,810
Gaew is just trying to be a better person.

713
00:46:05,920 --> 00:46:06,960
This house

714
00:46:06,960 --> 00:46:08,960
will always be ours.

715
00:46:09,510 --> 00:46:10,600
Our servants

716
00:46:10,910 --> 00:46:12,990
will always be ours.

717
00:46:13,680 --> 00:46:15,570
No one can take them away.

718
00:46:15,950 --> 00:46:19,670
He’s helping us take care of the servants.

719
00:46:19,670 --> 00:46:20,760
Isn’t that great?

720
00:46:23,950 --> 00:46:26,470
Let him do that.

721
00:46:31,740 --> 00:46:32,900
Ahem.

722
00:46:40,030 --> 00:46:41,870
This is just a common chickenpox.

723
00:46:42,420 --> 00:46:43,030
Yam.

724
00:46:43,350 --> 00:46:44,860
Bring me some herbs.

725
00:46:44,860 --> 00:46:48,910
I want turmeric, betel leaves, and coriander roots.

726
00:46:48,910 --> 00:46:49,930
Yes, sir.

727
00:46:50,600 --> 00:46:52,030
I’ll make an ointment for you.

728
00:46:53,030 --> 00:46:54,470
Don’t worry, guys.

729
00:46:54,890 --> 00:46:56,520
This isn’t a serious illness.

730
00:46:56,520 --> 00:46:58,040
You’ll recover soon.

731
00:46:59,920 --> 00:47:02,990
He has no respect for you, my lady.

732
00:47:03,530 --> 00:47:04,920
Look at him.

733
00:47:05,600 --> 00:47:06,320
And you.

734
00:47:07,420 --> 00:47:09,030
You should try to lose some weight.

735
00:47:10,730 --> 00:47:11,790
He's talking to you.

736
00:47:11,790 --> 00:47:12,750
No, you.

737
00:47:13,260 --> 00:47:14,840
Both of you.

738
00:47:14,840 --> 00:47:17,070
Be careful of fatty liver disease.

739
00:47:17,070 --> 00:47:20,030
As you get older, your arteries can clog.

740
00:47:20,830 --> 00:47:22,600
Which causes a heart attack.

741
00:47:22,600 --> 00:47:24,030
But don’t worry.

742
00:47:24,030 --> 00:47:26,190
If you pay attention to your diet…

743
00:47:26,190 --> 00:47:27,850
Just you wait, Gaew.

744
00:47:27,850 --> 00:47:29,690
I won’t let this slide.

745
00:47:55,210 --> 00:47:56,920
You’re just in time, Dech.

746
00:47:57,830 --> 00:47:59,040
What’s going on?

747
00:48:00,170 --> 00:48:00,960
Bua.

748
00:48:01,500 --> 00:48:02,870
Why are you crying?

749
00:48:06,420 --> 00:48:08,070
This servant…

750
00:48:08,550 --> 00:48:10,270
is pregnant with Gaew’s child.

751
00:48:22,560 --> 00:48:23,190
Prik.

752
00:48:24,580 --> 00:48:26,330
Go bring Gaew to me.

753
00:48:26,330 --> 00:48:27,180
Yes.

754
00:48:28,650 --> 00:48:29,500
You.

755
00:48:29,500 --> 00:48:30,230
You go.

756
00:48:43,420 --> 00:48:44,350
Pregnant?

757
00:48:50,360 --> 00:48:51,530
With my child?

758
00:48:54,440 --> 00:48:55,540
I’ve never…

759
00:48:55,540 --> 00:48:58,120
Enough with the excuses.

760
00:48:58,120 --> 00:49:00,140
You got her pregnant.

761
00:49:00,140 --> 00:49:03,080
You have to take responsibility.

762
00:49:16,620 --> 00:49:17,790
Father. Mother.

763
00:49:18,540 --> 00:49:19,520
I’m back.

764
00:49:26,150 --> 00:49:26,910
P’Sri.

765
00:49:27,960 --> 00:49:30,270
Sri, you’re back.

766
00:49:34,490 --> 00:49:35,360
Oh?

767
00:49:37,370 --> 00:49:38,950
Did Gaew cause trouble again?

768
00:50:26,300 --> 00:50:29,100
This is unripe durian fried until crispy.

769
00:50:29,330 --> 00:50:30,520
What is this?

770
00:50:31,010 --> 00:50:32,470
Is this really fried durian?

771
00:50:33,120 --> 00:50:37,010
How did I live without it before?

772
00:50:38,540 --> 00:50:39,750
Stay here.

773
00:50:40,800 --> 00:50:41,620
P’Muen?

774
00:50:42,150 --> 00:50:43,500
I think you’re…

775
00:50:43,500 --> 00:50:44,520
cuter now?

776
00:50:46,310 --> 00:50:46,970
My lord!

777
00:50:46,970 --> 00:50:47,690
Gaew!

778
00:50:47,690 --> 00:50:49,800
My lord, lord Muen went underwater.
